{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ASwdmrEDiphNZ4vD32V7BN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Verification Proof: Story 19-1 Epic Completion Detection\n2\t\n3\t**Story:** 19-1-epic-completion-detection\n4\t**Tier:** test-provable\n5\t**Date:** 2026-04-04\n6\t**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n7\t\n8\t## Build Verification\n9\t\n10\t- **Build (`npm run build`):** PASS — tsup compiled successfully, no errors.\n11\t- **Tests (`npm test`):** PASS — 4977 tests passed, 183 test files, 0 failures.\n12\t- **Lint (`npm run lint`):** WARN — 8 errors, 58 warnings (none in `epic-completion.ts`).\n13\t- **Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`):** PASS — All files 97.36% statements. `epic-completion.ts` has full test coverage (25 tests, all pass).\n14\t\n15\t## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n16\t\n17\t## AC 1: Module exports `checkEpicCompletion`, `getEpicStories`, `transitionEpicState`\n18\t**Result:** PASS\n19\t**Evidence:** `src/lib/epic-completion.ts` exists (3780 bytes). Exports confirmed:\n20\t- `export function checkEpicCompletion(state: SprintState, epicId: string): boolean`\n21\t- `export function getEpicStories(state: SprintState, epicId: string): string[]`\n22\t- `export function transitionEpicState(state: SprintState, epicId: string, targetStatus: EpicLifecycleStatus): SprintState`\n23\t- Test: \"exports checkEpicCompletion, getEpicStories, transitionEpicState\" PASS\n24\t\n25\t## AC 2: `checkEpicCompletion` returns `true` when all stories are `done`\n26\t**Result:** PASS\n27\t**Evidence:** Test \"returns true when all stories are done\" PASS\n28\t\n29\t## AC 3: `checkEpicCompletion` returns `false` when any story is not `done`\n30\t**Result:** PASS\n31\t**Evidence:** Test \"returns false when any story is not done\" PASS\n32\t\n33\t## AC 4: `transitionEpicState` updates status and `storiesDone` on `completing` transition\n34\t**Result:** PASS\n35\t**Evidence:** Tests \"returns updated state with new status\" and \"updates storiesDone on completing transition\" both PASS\n36\t\n37\t## AC 5: `getEpicStories` filters by numeric prefix before first dash\n38\t**Result:** PASS\n39\t**Evidence:** Tests \"filters correctly by epic ID prefix\", \"does not include stories from other epics\", and \"does not match epic 1 against story 19-1-foo\" all PASS\n40\t\n41\t## AC 6: `EpicLifecycleStatus` includes all six values\n42\t**Result:** PASS\n43\t**Evidence:** Type definition confirmed in source: `'in-progress' | 'completing' | 'merging' | 'validating' | 'done' | 'failed'`. Test \"includes all six values\" PASS\n44\t\n45\t## AC 7: Invalid transition throws `EpicCompletionError`\n46\t**Result:** PASS\n47\t**Evidence:** Test \"throws on invalid transition\" PASS. Source confirms descriptive message: `Invalid transition: ${currentStatus} -> ${targetStatus}`\n48\t\n49\t## AC 8: Valid transitions match specified state machine\n50\t**Result:** PASS\n51\t**Evidence:** `VALID_TRANSITIONS` in source matches spec: `in-progress -> completing -> merging -> validating -> done`, plus `completing|merging|validating -> failed`. Test \"encodes the correct state machine\" PASS\n52\t\n53\t## AC 9: Non-existent epic throws `EpicCompletionError`\n54\t**Result:** PASS\n55\t**Evidence:** Tests \"throws EpicCompletionError for non-existent epic\" (checkEpicCompletion) and \"throws for non-existent epic\" (transitionEpicState) both PASS\n56\t\n57\t## AC 10: Epic with zero stories returns `false`\n58\t**Result:** PASS\n59\t**Evidence:** Test \"returns false for epic with zero stories\" PASS. Source line 87: `if (stories.length === 0) return false;`\n60\t\n61\t## Summary\n62\t\n63\t| Check | Result |\n64\t|-------|--------|\n65\t| Build | PASS |\n66\t| Tests | PASS (4977/4977) |\n67\t| Lint | WARN (8 errors, 58 warnings — none in story files) |\n68\t| Coverage | PASS (97.36% overall) |\n69\t| AC 1 | PASS |\n70\t| AC 2 | PASS |\n71\t| AC 3 | PASS |\n72\t| AC 4 | PASS |\n73\t| AC 5 | PASS |\n74\t| AC 6 | PASS |\n75\t| AC 7 | PASS |\n76\t| AC 8 | PASS |\n77\t| AC 9 | PASS |\n78\t| AC 10 | PASS |\n79\t\n80\t**Final Result: ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)**\n81\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb820906-0735-4f53-a851-3960824caad6","uuid":"366a778c-06e6-4aa4-8db0-53f765392c2f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:07:31.239Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/19-1-epic-completion-detection-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: Story 19-1 Epic Completion Detection\n\n**Story:** 19-1-epic-completion-detection\n**Tier:** test-provable\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n## Build Verification\n\n- **Build (`npm run build`):** PASS — tsup compiled successfully, no errors.\n- **Tests (`npm test`):** PASS — 4977 tests passed, 183 test files, 0 failures.\n- **Lint (`npm run lint`):** WARN — 8 errors, 58 warnings (none in `epic-completion.ts`).\n- **Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`):** PASS — All files 97.36% statements. `epic-completion.ts` has full test coverage (25 tests, all pass).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n## AC 1: Module exports `checkEpicCompletion`, `getEpicStories`, `transitionEpicState`\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** `src/lib/epic-completion.ts` exists (3780 bytes). Exports confirmed:\n- `export function checkEpicCompletion(state: SprintState, epicId: string): boolean`\n- `export function getEpicStories(state: SprintState, epicId: string): string[]`\n- `export function transitionEpicState(state: SprintState, epicId: string, targetStatus: EpicLifecycleStatus): SprintState`\n- Test: \"exports checkEpicCompletion, getEpicStories, transitionEpicState\" PASS\n\n## AC 2: `checkEpicCompletion` returns `true` when all stories are `done`\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Test \"returns true when all stories are done\" PASS\n\n## AC 3: `checkEpicCompletion` returns `false` when any story is not `done`\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Test \"returns false when any story is not done\" PASS\n\n## AC 4: `transitionEpicState` updates status and `storiesDone` on `completing` transition\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Tests \"returns updated state with new status\" and \"updates storiesDone on completing transition\" both PASS\n\n## AC 5: `getEpicStories` filters by numeric prefix before first dash\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Tests \"filters correctly by epic ID prefix\", \"does not include stories from other epics\", and \"does not match epic 1 against story 19-1-foo\" all PASS\n\n## AC 6: `EpicLifecycleStatus` includes all six values\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Type definition confirmed in source: `'in-progress' | 'completing' | 'merging' | 'validating' | 'done' | 'failed'`. Test \"includes all six values\" PASS\n\n## AC 7: Invalid transition throws `EpicCompletionError`\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Test \"throws on invalid transition\" PASS. Source confirms descriptive message: `Invalid transition: ${currentStatus} -> ${targetStatus}`\n\n## AC 8: Valid transitions match specified state machine\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** `VALID_TRANSITIONS` in source matches spec: `in-progress -> completing -> merging -> validating -> done`, plus `completing|merging|validating -> failed`. Test \"encodes the correct state machine\" PASS\n\n## AC 9: Non-existent epic throws `EpicCompletionError`\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Tests \"throws EpicCompletionError for non-existent epic\" (checkEpicCompletion) and \"throws for non-existent epic\" (transitionEpicState) both PASS\n\n## AC 10: Epic with zero stories returns `false`\n**Result:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Test \"returns false for epic with zero stories\" PASS. Source line 87: `if (stories.length === 0) return false;`\n\n## Summary\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Build | PASS |\n| Tests | PASS (4977/4977) |\n| Lint | WARN (8 errors, 58 warnings — none in story files) |\n| Coverage | PASS (97.36% overall) |\n| AC 1 | PASS |\n| AC 2 | PASS |\n| AC 3 | PASS |\n| AC 4 | PASS |\n|